HEADWORD: Tennantite
<hw>Ten"nant*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Named after
<person>Smithson <etsep>Tennant</etsep></person>, an English
chemist.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A blackish lead-gray mineral,
closely related to tetrahedrite. It is essentially a sulphide of arsenic
and copper.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

